If your blog has a sidebar, you should try to utilize that space wisely.



5

00:00:14.100 --> 00:00:19.350

The very first thing in your sidebar, in most cases should be an opt in form.



6

00:00:19.560 --> 00:00:24.810

This is something that's going to be visible on every page, at least for your desktop visitors and



7

00:00:24.810 --> 00:00:27.270

people expect to see an opt in form there.



8

00:00:27.270 --> 00:00:31.260

So if they're looking for it, that'll probably be the first place they check.



9

00:00:32.010 --> 00:00:38.340

A lot of bloggers failed to capture leads at the end of their posts, and they're missing a huge opportunity



10

00:00:38.340 --> 00:00:38.610

there.



11

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:44.370

If somebody reads all the way to the end of your post, they're clearly engaged with your content.



12

00:00:44.370 --> 00:00:50.100

So that's a perfect place to ask them to join your list by offering some kind of free resource.



13

